{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ῥίζ-α</b>, ης, ἡ: <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>nominative</i> ῥίζη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus cited in 1st c.AD: Erotianus Grammaticus, _accusative_ ῥίζην 2nd c.AD: Marcellus Sidetes Poeta Medicus 89 (before a vowel), but ῥίζαν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.846 (whence _Ionic dialect_ _nominative_ ῥίζα may be inferred)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>root</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.304, 23.196, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; used as a medicine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.846 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ῥ. ἐλατήριος, of a purgative medicine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 5.34 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: mostly in <i>plural</i>, <b>roots</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.134, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.435, etc.; δένδρεα μακρὰ αὐτῇσιν ῥίζησι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.542: hence \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>roots of the eye</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.390 (but ῥίζας ἐν ὄσσοις αἱματῶπας in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 933 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] probably bloodshot <b>streaks</b>); the <b>roots</b> or <b>foundations</b> of the earth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 19; χθόνα.. αὐταῖς ῥ. πνεῦμα κραδαίνοι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1047 (_anapaest meter_); ἰπούμενος ῥίζαισιν Αἰτναίαις ὕπο [prev. work] 367 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of feathers, hair, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 251b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 518b14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the teeth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “GA” 789a13; γαστρὸς ῥ. ὀμφαλός [prev. author] “HA” 493a18, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> τὸν πόλεμον ἐκ ῥιζῶν ἀνῄρηκε 'root and branch', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 21, compare 4th c.AD: Heraclides Historicus Pont. cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 12.523f; ἐκ ῥιζῶν ἀπώλεσεν LXX.Job.31.12 \">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]; compare ῥιζόθεν, πρόρριζος. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>that from which anything springs as from a root</b>, ῥίζαν ἀπείρου τρίταν a third continental <b>foundation</b>, of Libya, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 9.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀστέων ῥ., of Cyrene, as the <b>root</b> or <b>original</b> of the Cyrenaic Pentapolis, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 4.15 \">Refs</a>]; <b>root</b> or <b>stock</b> from which a family springs, ῥ. σπέρματος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “O.” 2.46, compare “I.” 8(7).61, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 966, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1178, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so, <b>race, family</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 755 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 610, “OGI” 383.31 (Nemrud Dagh, 2nd c.BC), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; συκοφάντου.. σπέρμα καὶ ῥ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.48 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>sect, party</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “contra Galilaeos” 106e; also ῥ. κακῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 912.11 (_anapaest meter_); ἀρχὴ καὶ ῥ. παντὸς ἀγαθοῦ 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 409, cf. NT.1Tim.6.10; πηγὴ καὶ ῥ. καλοκἀγαθίας 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.4c; ἀρχαὶ καὶ ῥ. γῆς καὶ θαλάττης 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 353b1, etc.; compare ῥίζωμα 11. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>base, foundation</b>, ῥ. πάντων καὶ βάσις ἁ γᾶ ἐρήρεισται Ti. <i>Locrian dialect</i>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 97e,compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 81c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>base</b> of a vertical pillar, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “Hypotyposis astronomicarum positionum” 3.23; τῶν λόφων 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 10.6. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> in Mathematics texts, <b>root</b> or <b>base</b> of a series, Anatolius cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Theologumena Arithmeticae” 9\">Refs</a>]. (<i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>βρίζα</b> (which see): cf. Gothic <i>waúrts</i>, Latin <i>radix.</i>)","strongNumber":"G4491","accentedUnicode":"ῥίζα","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4492","matchingForm":"ῥιζόω","stepTransliteration":"rizoō","gloss":"to root","_zh_tw_Gloss":"生根","_es_Gloss":"arraigar","_zh_Gloss":"生根"}],"shortDef":"root, rootstock","mediumDef":"root, rootstock <br /><b>a root</b>, of a tree, <ref='Mat.3.10; 13:6'>Mt. 3:10; 13:6</ref>; met. <greek>ἔχειν ῥιζαν</greek>, or <greek>ἔχειν ῥιζαν ἐν ἑαυτῶ</greek>, <b>to be rooted</b> in faith, <ref='Mat.13.21'>Mt. 13:21</ref>; <ref='Mrk.4.17'>Mk. 4:17</ref>; <ref='Luk.8.13'>Lk. 8:13</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <b>cause, source, origin,</b> <ref='1Ti.6.10'>1Tim. 6:10;</ref> <ref='Heb.12.15'>Heb. 12:15;</ref> by <i>synecdoche</i> <b>the trunk, stock</b> of a tree, <i>metaphorically</i> <ref='Rom.11.16, 17, 18'>Rom. 11:16, 17, 18</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <b>offspring, progeny, a descendant,</b> <ref='Rom.15.12'>Rom. 15:12;</ref> <ref='Rev.5.5'>Rev. 5:5;</ref> 22:16","stepGloss":"root","stepTransliteration":"riza","count":17,"_es_Definition":"raíz ; descendiente ; fuente, causa (de maldad)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 樹根<br>2) 幼株, 新芽, 嫩枝: 在新